==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Franc
<hw>Franc</hw> <pr>(fr⟦acr⟧⟦nsm⟧k)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr.
<ets>franc</ets> a Franc. See <er>Frank</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety>
<def>A silver coin of France, and since 1795 the unit of the French
monetary system. It has been adopted by Belgium and Swizerland. In 1913
it was equivalent to about nineteen cents American, or ten pence
British, and is divided into 100 centimes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Franchise</ent>⟦br⟧
